# scripts/guards/check-scaffold-extension.allowlist
#
# Phase 0b.1b-ii-B (operator-authorized 2026-05-04) — lenient baseline.
# Each line is a pre-existing hand-written Zod schema in
# packages/shared/src/*.ts that has a matching migration-driven scaffold
# under packages/shared/src/_scaffolds/ but neither imports from the
# scaffold nor carries a `// @scaffold-divergence: <reason>` annotation.
#
# Format (per CLAUDE.md §11 + Phase 0a.7 expiry retrofit):
#   <file>:<schemaName>  # baseline 2026-05-04 | BUG-XXX — <reason> | expires: <YYYY-MM-DD> (cascade: <BUG>)
#
# 48 baseline entries seeded 2026-05-04 — all pre-existing in HEAD before
# Phase 0b.1b-ii-B's scaffold-extension guard landed. Drain umbrella:
# BUG-PHASE-0B-1B-II-B-CASCADE-DRAIN-SCAFFOLD-EXTENSION (S2). Drains as
# schemas migrate to the scaffold-extending pattern (per CLAUDE.md §15 +
# Phase 0b.1 plan):
#   1. Import the scaffold's exported `<table><Kind>ScaffoldSchema` from
#      `./_scaffolds/<table>.<dto|response>.scaffold`.
#   2. Build the hand-written schema as `<scaffold>.extend({...})` /
#      `.merge({...})` / `.pick({...})` / `.omit({...})`, OR
#   3. Add `// @scaffold-divergence: <reason>` at file or schema level.
#
# Then remove the entry from this file.
#
# NEW hand-written schemas with a matching scaffold cannot be allowlisted
# (the guard's stale-allowlist check rejects entries pointing to schemas
# that don't currently violate; the gold-standard L3 review at commit
# time blocks new violator additions).
#
# Expiry-policy: per-entry (added 2026-05-04 per Phase 0a.7 retrofit)
# Each non-comment line carries an `| expires: <YYYY-MM-DD> (cascade: <BUG>)`
# annotation. Entries past their expiry date fail the merge gate via
# `scripts/guards/check-allowlist-expiry.ts`.

